<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-12-31T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-12-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="323" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d323">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">Roosevelt Papers: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Roosevelt</persName>
                                to Prime Minister <persName type="to">Churchill</persName>
                            </hi><note n="1" xml:id="d323fn1">Sent to the United States Naval
                                Attaché, London, via Navy channels.</note>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                                <lb/>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">urgent—priority</hi>
                            </seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-12-31">December 31, 1942</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>From the President for the <gloss target="#t_FormerNavalPerson1">Former
                                Naval Person</gloss> personal and secret No. 248.</p>
                        <p>Arrangements for <gloss target="#t_Symbol1">
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Symbol</hi>
                            </gloss> satisfactory. Our Chiefs of Staff will arrive twelfth and I
                            will follow two days later so that we could all meet together on
                            fifteenth. I believe our staffs can cover the ground in a two day
                            preliminary conference. The prospect pleases me.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Roosevelt</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>